[DhtmlXQ_comment0]eg xqsycj tjm 073 2h1e sw 1c2a 01||When there is an elephant present to aid the two horses, they would be able to defeat the combination of one cannon and two advisors, especially when black's advisors are low advisors (on the throat rank and bottom rank), as in this example.||This is because the king would be affected by the advisors and have less room to maneuver.  ||Three examples are given in this series.[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
[DhtmlXQ_comment1]By retreating the elephant, the red king now controls the central file. ||The black advisors are now stunned and cannot move at all. That way, the black king cannot choose to move to his 4th or 6th file at will, making him prone to attack by the horses.[/DhtmlXQ_comment1]
[DhtmlXQ_comment2]If black chose to play K5=6, please refer to the next example for red's win.[/DhtmlXQ_comment2]
[DhtmlXQ_comment25]And red would checkmate with H4+6 on the next move.[/DhtmlXQ_comment25]
